BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Performance
DESCRIPTION:Written by Lauren Gunderson\nDirected by Josie Seid\n\nWednesda
 y-Saturday\, February 18-21 @ 7:30 PM\nSunday\, February 22 @ 2:00 PM\nMago
  Hunt Theater\n\n“Four beautiful\, badass women lose their heads in this ir
 reverent\, girl-powered comedy set during the French Revolution’s Reign of 
 Terror. Playwright Olympe de Gouges\, assassin Charlotte Corday\, former qu
 een (and fan of ribbons) Marie Antoinette\, and Haitian rebel Marianne Ange
 lle hang out\, murder Marat\, and try to beat back the extremist insanity i
 n 1793 Paris. This grand and dream-tweaked comedy is about violence and leg
 acy\, art and activism\, feminism and terrorism\, compatriots and chosen si
 sters\, and how we actually go about changing the world. It’s a true story.
  Or total fiction. Or a play about a play. Or a raucous resurrection…that e
 nds in a song and a scaffold.” – Dramatists Play Service\n\nSpecial Events:
 \n\nAlum-Night: Friday\, February 20\, 2026. Garaventa Pre-Show Panel and R
 eception: Saturday\, February 21\, 2026Tickets are on sale now! Use code 'F
 IRST50' for $5 tickets\, or 'PRESALE' for $10 tickets. Contact boxoffice@up
 .edu with any questions.
DTEND:20260221T043000Z
DTSTAMP:20260312T160901Z
DTSTART:20260221T033000Z
GEO:45.573252;-122.728181
LOCATION:Mago Hunt Center\, Theater
SEQUENCE:0
