BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Performance,Social Gathering / Reception
DESCRIPTION:Ticket show holders for UP's theater production of The Revoluti
 onists may enjoy a complimentary small bites reception and an expert pre-sh
 ow panel discussion. Ticket purchase HERE. Saturday\, February 21\, Mago Hu
 nt Center. Reception at 6:15pm\; Panel Discussion from 6:45-7:15pm\; Show a
 t 7:30pm. For more information and ADA accommodations contact garaventa@up.
 edu and 503-943-7702.\n\nAbout The Revolutionists: “Four beautiful\, badass
  women lose their heads in this irreverent\, girl-powered comedy set during
  the French Revolution’s Reign of Terror. Playwright Olympe de Gouges\, ass
 assin Charlotte Corday\, former queen (and fan of ribbons) Marie Antoinette
 \, and Haitian rebel Marianne Angelle hang out\, murder Marat\, and try to 
 beat back the extremist insanity in 1793 Paris. This grand and dream-tweake
 d comedy is about violence and legacy\, art and activism\, feminism and ter
 rorism\, compatriots and chosen sisters\, and how we actually go about chan
 ging the world. It’s a true story. Or total fiction. Or a play about a play
 . Or a raucous resurrection…that ends in a song and a scaffold.” – Dramatis
 ts Play Service
