BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Academic,Lecture / Presentation / Talk
DESCRIPTION:Discover the beauty of the first illuminated\, handwritten Bibl
 e to be commissioned in more than 500 years through the Heritage Edition wi
 th the director of The Saint John’s Bible Heritage Program\, Brad Neary. Ea
 ch Heritage Edition is unique and features the exquisite calligraphy\, vibr
 ant imagery and stunning gold and silver illuminations inspired by the orig
 inal manuscript of The Saint John’s Bible. \n\nIn all\, only 299 seven-volu
 me Heritage Editions have been created\, and because many of the 160 major 
 illuminations were hand-finished\, each Heritage Edition is unique. Donald 
 Jackson was the creative director in making these limited editions and thro
 ugh his meticulous attention to every aspect of its production\, the herita
 ge Edition is true to the artistic intent of the original. These beautiful 
 volumes are used in worship\, academics\, fine arts and community outreach.
 \n\nJoin us as we ignite our spiritual imaginations with UP’s very own Sain
 t John’s Bible Heritage Edition.\n\nFree and open to the public. For more i
 nfo or ADA accommodations contact garaventa@up.edu or 503-943-7702.
DTEND:20260224T223000Z
DTSTAMP:20260312T160901Z
DTSTART:20260224T213000Z
GEO:45.572806;-122.726753
LOCATION:Clark Library\, Clark Library Classroom
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Ignite Your Spiritual Imagination with "The Saint John's Bible"
